Mwingi Central MP aspirant Gideon Mulyungi (Wiper) has promised Ukasi residents he will end banditry.Those affected will also be compensated, he added. Mulyungi said he is prepared to safeguard the community. He previously sued the government after some Ukasi residents were killed in Sosoma and other areas on the Kitui- Tana River border. The case hearing has been slated for June 17.